story.title: Love, Virtually - Episode 3
story.storyDescription: Can two competing players in the world of online gaming overcome obstacles, both real and virtually, and come together?
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Jonathan Rosen is a transplanted New Yorker, who now lives with his family in sunny, South Florida. He's been writing ever since he was a little kid, but it's much more legible now.

story.prePaywallNotification: Tap back into Hooked to see what FaerieQueen’s future reveals!
story.postPaywallNotification: Things are getting personal in LOVE, VIRTUALLY…keep reading to see what happens next!

messages.text: Wait a second. I can’t go look up your future. Isn’t that against the law or something?
What law? There’s a law against looking up your future?
In like EVERY time travel movie EVER! They tell you it’s bad to look up your future.
You’re not looking up your future. You’re looking up mine.
Ha! That’s semantics. Doc Brown wouldn’t approve of you!
Who?
Seriously??
OMG! I’m kidding! Yes, I’ve seen Back to the Future. You are so gullible!
Okay, okay. You got me. But, that doesn’t change things. They always say it’s bad to look up your future.
Yeah, but that’s for looking up things like sports results or for making money. That’s a taboo. Not if you just want to get a little sneak peek of something.
Wait. Are you putting amendments to the time rule? You can’t do that! 😊
I’m just curious. I promise you I won’t gamble or anything.
That’s not the point. I’m talking about everyday little things.
Let’s say that you’re supposed to go somewhere and save someone’s life, and I tell you that it’s going to pour tomorrow, so you stay inside instead of going out.
That means you changed the future, and that person you were supposed to save, now dies.
This is a lot of responsibility.
You’re overthinking this.
I guess it’s a good thing I don’t know anything personal about you, since then I might be tempted.
Jessica.
What?
My name is Jessica Harris. And you?
I guess your rule about keeping things personal is gone.
You’ve proven yourself.
What’s your name?
Brandon Moore.
One second.
What are you doing? Looking me up? 😊
Yes.
Really? Then I’m looking you up!
There are a few here on Facebook. Which one is you?
I’m trying to think back then.
Oh. I remember. I’m in a Dodgers cap and if I remember right, there’s a girl next to me.
Redhead?
Yeah.
Cute. You both are. Who is she? Your wife?
Yes. My ex.
So, you were still together in 2018?
I think at that time, we had been divorced for a few months already.I had just stayed off social media for a while.
Speaking of which, I’m not sure which Jessica Harris is you.
I don’t know what picture I would have then, but now it’s a picture of me as a little girl in front of the ice skating rink at Rockefeller Center.
No, I definitely don’t see that.
I believe that. I go through periods where I deactivate my account, when I get tired of the drama. And there’s always drama.
You don’t have one of you and your boyfriend/fiancé?
No. Long story.
Well, we have two years’ worth of time to catch up on. 😊
I guess I could tell you, since there’s no way you could let anyone know now.
Sometimes, I just don’t know what I want.
But, you’re engaged to him.
Yeah, I know. You ever just get comfortable in a relationship and don’t make a move?
Of course. Most of us have. I think my marriage was like that.
What happened?
The same thing. At the beginning, everything was great, and then it went downhill. Fast.
And then you realize the beginning wasn’t that great either. You settled for years because both of you were too scared to make a move.
I’m literally sighing. That’s exactly my fear. I think I love him, but I also think it’s more comfort than anything else.
That’s kind of sad.
Tell me about it. I keep going back and forth in my mind. I don’t know what to do.
Jessica, you can’t get married if you feel like that. Trust me.
Who called it off with you?
Actually, she did. We were both feeling it, but she finally came home one day and asked to talk.
That’s NEVER a good sign.
No, it never is.
So, basically, you got off easy.
There was nothing easy about it.
Yeah, but would you have done it if she didn’t bring it up?
I don’t know.
Like I said, you got off easy. I feel the same way. I go back and forth with it. He’s a good guy. I’m just not sure he’s the right guy.
But, you’ll still marry him.
I guess.
Have you talked about a wedding?
HA!! Yeah, and it’s sooner than I want to tell you about.
Let’s talk about you. Did she have someone on the side when she broke it off with you?
BTW, I still can’t find you.
I can’t believe you’re still looking!
It’s not fair that you see me, and I don’t see you!
You’re avoiding my question.
I don’t know if she was cheating on me. I don’t think so, but she did start dating someone soon after.
I don’t know, it sounds like she had someone.
At that point, it didn’t matter. There was no point in holding onto something that wasn’t there.
I agree. I figure, there are plenty of people who want to be with me, I don’t need to hold onto someone who doesn’t.
That’s exactly what I thought.
You with anyone now?
No. But not because I’m not over her. Just haven’t found the right person.
It’ll come.
Jessica, is your fiancé’s name Michael?
Get out! You found me?
Yeah.
Oh, come on! I told you!
Unless you don’t think I’m cute, then don’t tell me.
It’s not that.
Then, what is it?
Jessica, if this is you, it says that you’re going to die in two days.
